  "product_overview": "Hospital Management System (HMS) is a comprehensive, secure, and scalable PHP-based application designed to streamline hospital operations covering patient care, staff management, clinical workflows, financial accounting, and supply chain processes through modular APIs and a unified dashboard.",
  "core_goals": [
    "Develop a secure authentication and role-based access control system for hospital staff.",
    "Implement core hospital operational modules including patient management, staff management, appointment scheduling, admissions, and bed management.",
    "Digitize clinical workflows such as surgery scheduling and pharmacy management for efficient resource usage.",
    "Build a robust financial and supply chain management system integrating billing and invoicing with operational modules.",
    "Provide comprehensive dashboards and business intelligence reports for decision-making support.",
    "Ensure system-wide integration, security hardening, and performance optimization through iterative testing and audits.",
    "Deliver detailed documentation and training for hospital staff to ensure smooth adoption."
  ],
  "key_features": [
    "Authentication API with secure login/logout and session management.",
    "Patient Management API to handle patient registration, updates, and medical records.",
    "Appointment Management for scheduling, viewing, and managing patient appointments with doctors.",
    "Admission and Bed Management to admit patients, assign beds, and track ward capacity.",
    "Staff Management module for hospital personnel including doctors, nurses, and administrators with role assignments.",
    "Billing API enabling patient billing, payment processing, and insurance claim integration.",
    "Pharmacy Management for inventory control, prescriptions, and medication dispensing workflows.",
    "Surgery API for scheduling surgeries, managing operating rooms, and surgical personnel.",
    "Ward and Bed Management APIs to efficiently administer hospital ward capacities and bed assignments.",
    "Supply Management to track medical supplies, vendors, and inventory levels.",
    "Business Intelligence APIs generating reports on patient statistics, financials, and occupancy.",
    "Dashboard API providing overview and real-time hospital operation statistics.",
    "Home API serving general hospital information and landing content."
  ],
  "user_flow_summary": [
    "User logs in securely via the Authentication API, gaining access based on role permissions.",
    "Staff members are managed by HR through the Staff Management API linking user accounts and roles.",
    "Patients are registered and their information updated using the Patient Management API.",
    "Receptionists schedule and update patient appointments with doctors via the Appointment Management API.",
    "Patients admitted through the Admission API are assigned beds and wards via the Bed and Ward Management APIs.",
    "Clinical staff schedule surgeries and manage operating room allocations using the Surgery API.",
    "Pharmacy staff manage drug inventory and dispense medications using the Pharmacy API linked with patient prescriptions.",
    "Billing staff generate bills and process payments associated with patient treatments through the Billing API.",
    "Hospital administrators access real-time dashboards and business intelligence reports to monitor performance and resource utilization.",
    "System-wide data integration supports seamless workflows from patient registration to discharge and billing.",
    "End users provide feedback during User Acceptance Testing to ensure system meets operational needs."
  ],
  "validation_criteria": [
    "All APIs conform to OpenAPI 3.0 specification with comprehensive endpoint coverage and parameter validation.",
    "Authentication system securely hashes passwords and manages sessions with no unauthorized access.",
    "Patient, staff, appointment, admission, and billing data are persistently and correctly stored in MySQL database following normalization rules.",
    "Integration testing confirms data flows seamlessly between modules (e.g., patient registration to billing).",
    "Security audits verify prevention of common vulnerabilities including SQL injection and cross-site scripting (XSS).",
    "Performance benchmarks show optimized queries and minimal latency with caching strategies implemented.",
    "User Acceptance Testing confirms usability, accuracy, and workflow alignment for hospital staff roles.",
    "Documentation includes detailed user manuals for each module and administration guides.",
    "Deployment performed successfully with production environment validation ensuring system stability and uptime.",
    "Business Intelligence reports accurately reflect hospital KPIs such as bed occupancy rate, average length of stay, and financial metrics."
  ],
